HEADWORD: Wenlock group
<hw>Wen"lock group`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The
middle subdivision of the Upper Silurian in Great Britain; -- so named
from the typical locality in Shropshire.</def>⟦br⟧
